The paper deals with named entity recognition, which is a task in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses graph convolutional networks (GCN), which are a type of neural network commonly used in machine learning (ML) tasks such as image recognition and natural language processing. This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), or cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper focuses on the role of dependency trees in NER, which is a specific aspect of NLP, suggesting that cs.NE (Natural Language Processing) is also a possible sub-category.
